The paper deals with object recognition using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of universal adversarial perturbations, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the limitations of current approaches and proposes a new method, which could be considered as a critique or improvement of existing methods, making it relevant to computer security (cs.CR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
